{
  "texts": [
    "Such a violation of assumption iii arguably leads to an underestimation of the number of false positives and, vice versa, to precision overestimation.",
    "To compensate for this, we used (i) relatively strict precision thresholds, (ii) multiple baseline periods and (iii) penalties for the precision thresholds if not all baseline periods were accessible.",
    "Baseline periodsUsing multiple baseline periods may be considered the most effective tool in addressing violation of assumption iii, as they increase the likelihood that at least one of them validly reproduces the background noise during the story period.",
    "We considered up to n = 4 baseline periods (but at least two), depending on whether these periods were available (a baseline period may be not available because Twitter was, for instance, not launched at this time).",
    "A baseline period b j is defined via two points in time b o j and b e j, both extratemporal and with the same duration as the story (we used Ṫ = Ṫ e -Ṫ o to estimate the duration)."
  ]
}